006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.binding.metaschema;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.adapter.PositiveIntegerAdapter;
009import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.adapter.StringAdapter;
010import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.adapter.TokenAdapter;
011import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.markup.MarkupLine;
012import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.markup.MarkupLineAdapter;
013import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IBoundObject;
014import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IMetaschemaData;
015import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.JsonGroupAsBehavior;
016import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.constraint.IConstraint;
017import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.util.ObjectUtils;
018import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.AllowedValue;
019import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.AllowedValues;
020import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.BoundAssembly;
021import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.BoundField;
022import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.BoundFlag;
023import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.GroupAs;
024import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.MetaschemaAssembly;
025import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.databind.model.annotations.ValueConstraints;
026
027import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.ReflectionToStringBuilder;
028import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.ToStringStyle;
029
030import java.math.BigInteger;
031import java.util.LinkedList;
032import java.util.List;
033
034@SuppressWarnings({
035    "PMD.DataClass",
036    "PMD.FieldNamingConventions"
037})
038@MetaschemaAssembly(
039    formalName = "Flag Reference",
040    name = "flag-reference",
041    moduleClass = MetaschemaModelModule.class)
042public class FlagReference implements IBoundObject {
043  private final IMetaschemaData __metaschemaData;
044
045  @BoundFlag(
046      formalName = "Global Flag Reference",
047      name = "ref",
048      required = true,
049      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class)
050  private String _ref;
051
052  @BoundFlag(
053      formalName = "Flag Reference Binary Name",
054      name = "index",
055      typeAdapter = PositiveIntegerAdapter.class)
056  private BigInteger _index;
057
058  @BoundFlag(
059      formalName = "Deprecated Version",
060      name = "deprecated",
061      typeAdapter = StringAdapter.class)
062  private String _deprecated;
063
064  @BoundFlag(
065      formalName = "Default Flag Value",
066      name = "default",
067      typeAdapter = StringAdapter.class)
068  private String _default;
069
070  @BoundFlag(
071      formalName = "Is Flag Required?",
072      name = "required",
073      defaultValue = "no",
074      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
075      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR,
076          values = { @AllowedValue(value = "yes", description = ""), @AllowedValue(value = "no", description = "") })))
077  private String _required;
078
079  @BoundField(
080      formalName = "Formal Name",
081      description = "A formal name for the data construct, to be presented in documentation.",
082      useName = "formal-name")
083  private String _formalName;
084
085  @BoundField(
086      formalName = "Description",
087      description = "A short description of the data construct's purpose, describing the constructs semantics.",
088      useName = "description",
089      typeAdapter = MarkupLineAdapter.class)
090  private MarkupLine _description;
091
092  @BoundAssembly(
093      formalName = "Property",
094      useName = "prop",
095      maxOccurs = -1,
096      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "props", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
097  private List<Property> _props;
098
099  @BoundField(
100      formalName = "Use Name",
101      description = "Allows the name of the definition to be overridden.",
102      useName = "use-name")
103  private UseName _useName;
104
105  @BoundField(
106      formalName = "Remarks",
107      description = "Any explanatory or helpful information to be provided about the remarks parent.",
108      useName = "remarks")
109  private Remarks _remarks;
110
111  public FlagReference() {
112    this(null);
113  }
114
115  public FlagReference(IMetaschemaData data) {
116    this.__metaschemaData = data;
117  }
118
119  @Override
120  public IMetaschemaData getMetaschemaData() {
121    return __metaschemaData;
122  }
123
124  public String getRef() {
125    return _ref;
126  }
127
128  public void setRef(String value) {
129    _ref = value;
130  }
131
132  public BigInteger getIndex() {
133    return _index;
134  }
135
136  public void setIndex(BigInteger value) {
137    _index = value;
138  }
139
140  public String getDeprecated() {
141    return _deprecated;
142  }
143
144  public void setDeprecated(String value) {
145    _deprecated = value;
146  }
147
148  public String getDefault() {
149    return _default;
150  }
151
152  public void setDefault(String value) {
153    _default = value;
154  }
155
156  public String getRequired() {
157    return _required;
158  }
159
160  public void setRequired(String value) {
161    _required = value;
162  }
163
164  public String getFormalName() {
165    return _formalName;
166  }
167
168  public void setFormalName(String value) {
169    _formalName = value;
170  }
171
172  public MarkupLine getDescription() {
173    return _description;
174  }
175
176  public void setDescription(MarkupLine value) {
177    _description = value;
178  }
179
180  public List<Property> getProps() {
181    return _props;
182  }
183
184  public void setProps(List<Property> value) {
185    _props = value;
186  }
187
188  /**
189   * Add a new {@link Property} item to the underlying collection.
190   *
191   * @param item
192   *          the item to add
193   * @return {@code true}
194   */
195  public boolean addProp(Property item) {
196    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
197    if (_props == null) {
198      _props = new LinkedList<>();
199    }
200    return _props.add(value);
201  }
202
203  /**
204   * Remove the first matching {@link Property} item from the underlying
205   * collection.
206   *
207   * @param item
208   *          the item to remove
209   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
210   */
211  public boolean removeProp(Property item) {
212    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
213    return _props != null && _props.remove(value);
214  }
215
216  public UseName getUseName() {
217    return _useName;
218  }
219
220  public void setUseName(UseName value) {
221    _useName = value;
222  }
223
224  public Remarks getRemarks() {
225    return _remarks;
226  }
227
228  public void setRemarks(Remarks value) {
229    _remarks = value;
230  }
231
232  @Override
233  public String toString() {
234    return new ReflectionToStringBuilder(this, ToStringStyle.MULTI_LINE_STYLE).toString();
235  }
236}
